@node "Overview" "Overview"
@next "Installation"
@prev "Main"
@{b}@{u}Overview@{ub}@{uu}

 AppAssign allow to perfom assign easily, without  edit  manualy,  just  drop
 Icon of directory/volume on its AppIcon (or AppMenu).

 And with the list of assigns, you can see assigns in memory and if  you  can
 remove some one.

 It not eat lot of memory ans its was full @{"parametrable" link "Parameters" 0}.

 This program use the @{"bgui.library" link "bgui.library" 0}.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@next "Parameters"
@prev "Overview"
@{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

 Just click on the 'Install_English' icon and answer the questions.
@endnode

@node "Parameters" "Parameters"
@next "GUI"
@prev "Installation"
@{b}@{u}Parameters@{ub}@{uu}

 You can configure AppAssign with its Tool-types.


 APPICON_X= <nombre>            Horizontale position of AppIcon.
 APPICON_Y= <nombre>            Verticale position of AppIcon.

 APPICON_NAME                   Name of AppIcon.

 APPMENU_NAME                   Name of AppMenu.


 ACTIVATE=YES|NO                Allow  to  always  activate  the  assign-edit
                                gadget.


 COPYNAME=YES|NO                If  the  pathname  is  a  directory  (not   a
                                volume),    this   option   allow   to   copy
                                automatiquely the name of this  directory  in
                                the assign-edit gadget.


 CONFIRM=YES|NO                 Allow to confirm some action like removing of
                                Assign, save..

 CX_POPKEY                      Hotkey for main window.

 LIST_POPKEY                    Hotkey for Assign-List.
@endnode

@node "GUI" "GUI"
@next "Disclaimer"
@prev "Parameters"
@{b}@{u}GUI@{ub}@{uu}

 @{i}@{u}o Main GUI@{ui}@{uu}

   When you drop a directory or volume on AppIcon/AppMenu or when you perform
   the Hotkey combinaison, the main GUI open.



  @{bg fill} Assign @{bg back}          For edit name of assign.

  @{bg fill} to     @{bg back}          Path on which AppAssign will perfom assign.


  @{bg fill} Mode @{bg back}
      @{bg fill} Normal @{bg back}      Perform a normal assign.

      @{bg fill} Add    @{bg back}      Perform a ADD assign (see your AmigaDos manual).

      @{bg fill} Path   @{bg back}      Perform a PATH assign (see your AmigaDos manual).


  @{bg fill} Copy name @{bg back}       If the pathname is  a  directory  (not  a  volume),  this
                    button copy the name of this directory in the assign-edit
                    gadget. Because a lot of assign-name  is  the  same  than
                    directory-name. (MainActor: on .../MainActor).


  @{bg fill} Clear     @{bg back}       Clear the assign-edit gadget.


  @{bg fill} List      @{bg back}       Open list of assigns (see bellow).

  @{bg fill} Save to file @{bg back}    This button allow to  save  the  current-edit  assign  to
                    file, like User-Startup.
                    WARNING: It save the assign, but not perfom it in memory,
                    you must click on ASSIGN atfer.



  @{bg fill} Assign @{bg back}          Perform assign.

  @{bg fill} Cancel @{bg back}          Close window.

  @{bg fill} Quit   @{bg back}          Quit AppAssign.


 @{i}@{u}o List of assigns@{ui}@{uu}


  @{bg fill} Information     @{bg back} Display number of assigns.

  @{bg fill} List of assigns @{bg back} List of assigns.

  @{bg fill} Update          @{bg back} Update list of assigns.

  @{bg fill} Remove          @{bg back} Remove selected assign.
@endnode

